<TITLE> Govt starts <i> boro </i> rice procurement Wednesday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, April 15 (bdnews24.com)The government launches a drive Wednesday to procure 15 lakh tonnes of boro rice to help ease the growing food crisis, an official said. The government will buy rice at Tk 28, up from last year's Tk 18 per kg, according to a decision taken at a meeting of the food monitoring and planning committee at the Chief Adviser's Office. "The procurement drive will continue through August," acting food secretary Mollah Waheduzzaman told bdnews24.com Tuesday. The prices include 40 percent incentives to rice growers, the official said. Food adviser AMM Shawkat Ali presided over the meeting, where finance adviser AB Mirza Azizul Islam, agriculture adviser CS Karim, LGRD adviser Anwarul Iqbal and commerce adviser Hossain Zillur Rahman were present. The government bought 12 lakh tonnes of boro rice last year. bdnews2
